title: Community Organizer Interview
Application Type: I applied online. The process took 3 weeks. I interviewed at Texas Equal Access Fund (Dallas, TX) in Nov 2022
Interview Descriptions: It was a phone interview with the previous community organizer. She asked questions about why I think I would be a good match, what I knew about the company, what I knew about abortion laws in texas, what I thought about racism in health care. Asked if I was Comfortable working on the political side of abortion (rallying at the capital, protests, speaking with legislators, etc.) I moved on to a second interview.
Interview Questions: Tell me more about yourself? Why do you think you would be a good match? What do you know about abortion? What is reproductive justice? How to do work on being antiracist? Do you have any political experience?
